Description:
printf_frexpl() function: split a long double into fraction and mantissa,
for hexadecimal printf, without requiring libm.

Files:
lib/printf-frexpl.h
lib/printf-frexpl.c
lib/printf-frexp.c
m4/printf-frexpl.m4
m4/ldexpl.m4
m4/longdouble.m4

Depends-on:
math
fpucw

configure.ac:
gl_FUNC_PRINTF_FREXPL

Makefile.am:
lib_SOURCES += printf-frexpl.c

Include:
#if HAVE_LONG_DOUBLE
# include "printf-frexpl.h"
#endif

License:
LGPL

Maintainer:
Bruno Haible

